# 6. 私に伝えられること

Len: <Huh? Shizuku, you're back already?>
Airi: That was quick. Were the baths not open yet?
Shizuku: No, they were...
Shizuku: But there's something I need to discuss with all of you.
Luka: <Did something happen just now?>
Shizuku: Yes, so...
Haruka: I see... Saito's grandmother is okay with her granddaughter not taking over because she wants her to be happy.
Airi: Then, doesn't that give Saito the green light to start pursuing her dream?
Minori: But... She still said she was gonna take over even after she heard what her grandmother had to say.
Shizuku: Exactly. Which is why...I'm not sure as to what to do right now.
Shizuku: This is a family matter, so we don't really have any right to butt in... But if she goes through with this, I feel that neither she nor her family will end up benefitting.
Airi: Right...
MEIKO: <But I'm still confused as to why she's so set on taking over running this inn.>
Miku: <Hmm... Saito's mother did say she's looking forward to her becoming the next proprietress. Maybe she doesn't want to let her down?>
Len: <I think that's only a part of it. I'm guessing that she feels a sense of duty.>
Len: <Remember what she said when we first got here...? She said, “I'm an only child...”>
Shizuku: Expectations... Duty...
Shizuku: I think I understand how she feels.
Haruka: Huh...?
Shizuku: Because when I was still in Cheerful * Days, I felt that I couldn't disappoint anyone and that I had a duty to fulfill.
KAITO: <Oh...>
Shizuku: Before I became an idol, I wasn't nearly as good a speaker as Airi was, and it always took me so long to make any decisions...
Shizuku: Because of that, I couldn't accept myself like I do now.
Shizuku: But my friends submitted an application to audition for me, and I somehow ended up winning the Grand Prix...
Shizuku: When I did, I finally came to the belief that even someone like me could help others by being an idol.
MEIKO: <Shizuku...>
Shizuku: That's why I felt that I couldn't disappoint anyone back then...
Shizuku: After that, I was chosen to become the lead, which gave me a strong sense of needing to fulfill my duty. And while those feelings did fuel me for a time...
Shizuku: As you all know, they weren't enough to keep me going.
KAITO: <Right...>
Shizuku: I don't want Saito to suffer the same fate.
Shizuku: So, if it's going to make everyone happy in the end, then I want Saito to pursue her real dreams...
Len: <Why don't you tell her what you just said?>
Shizuku: What...?
Haruka: I agree... I think she'd respond really well to what you just said.
Airi: I mean, Shizuku, I feel like you're the only one who can make all that clear to Saito. So I think you should go talk to her.
Shizuku: Only I can...?
Shizuku: Right. Then, I'll try talking to her.
Saito: Oh, it's already this late...?
Saito: (Wait, do we still have enough beer in stock? I need to check the inventory list after I'm done taking my break.)
Saito: (Then, I have to start prepping for breakfast. We're supposed to serve salmon tomorrow, so I'm sure Minori won't know what to do with herself, and...)
Saito: (My mind keeps wandering every chance it gets.)
Saito: I thought I'd gotten over all that yesterday...
Saito: ...
Saito: (Until just a little while ago, my event job partly felt almost like a hobby.)
Saito: (I gained such a huge interest in that line of work after shaking hands with Shizuku...)
Saito: (I knew that I'd have to take over here someday, so I figured even a part-time job in the industry would do. But...)
Saito: (Seeing everyone shine on stage and the way the crowd reacted... I wanted to make more of that happen. I was willing to give it everything I had.)
Saito: (I even started learning about how to be a manager. But I began taking things so seriously that I started forgetting about this place...)
Saito: (No, I didn't forget. I kept myself from remembering.)
Saito: Now I'm paying the price for that...
Saito: (I kept doing what I wanted to while pushing aside my obligations...)
Saito: (I knew that wouldn't last... I knew this time would come sooner or later.)
Saito: (But I have to forget about all that now. After all, I'm an only child...)
Saito: (I can't let my whims cause it to go out of business. And Mom's looking forward to me taking over.)
Saito: (So...I'm okay with my decision. I mean, I don't want this inn to close down.)
Saito: (Yes. This is fine.)
Saito: (Or... It should be...)
Young Child: Wait, Daddy, we're going home tomorrow?!
Father: Yes, honey. We're only here until tomorrow morning. After that, we'll be taking the car home.
Young Child: No, I don't wanna go! I wanna stay here forever!
Young Child: The food's so yummy! And the bathwater feels all weird and slippery! I really like it here! I don't wanna go!
Father: Haha. You're putting me in a tough spot. But we can always come again next year. Who knows? Maybe they'll serve something even more yummy and delicious then!
Young Child: Wait....really?! Then, we should come back again next year!
Saito: *Sigh* I should get back to work.
Saito: I need to check on our inventory and start prepping for breakfast while I still have—
???: Saito!
Saito: Huh...?
Shizuku: Do you have a minute to talk?
Saito: Shizuku...?
